OL,3,CLabour suffer losses and Reform make
OL,4,Cgains in early election results
OL,6,FReform leader Nigel Farage has already
OL,7,Fsuggested his party is on course for a
OL,8,Fgeneral election victory, comparing
OL,9,Fits early gains to clearing Becher's
OL,10,FBrook - a famously difficult jump in
OL,11,Fthe Grand National.
OL,13,FThe party gained its first council,
OL,14,Ftaking Newcastle-under-Lyme from the
OL,15,FConservatives.
OL,17,FFarage said: "This for me was our
OL,18,FBecher's Brook. If we cleared Becher's
OL,19,FBrook and landed well, we go on to win
OL,20,Fthe Grand National.
OL,26,@yD@NOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778328667
OL,3,CLabour suffer losses and Reform make
OL,4,Cgains in early election results
OL,6,F"What is very clear to me is that our
OL,7,Fvoters will stick with us now all the
OL,8,Fway through. They are not lending
OL,9,Ftheir vote to Reform."
OL,11,FSir Keir Starmer's party went into
OL,12,FThursday's local elections expected to
OL,13,Flose up to 1,850 councillors, with
OL,14,Fsenior figures describing the contest
OL,15,Fas "tough".
OL,17,FInitial results painted a bleak
OL,18,Fpicture for the prime minister, who is
OL,19,Falready receiving calls to step down.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@VO]wD@DOUwD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
