OL,3,CLabour suffer losses and Reform make
OL,4,Cgains in early election results
OL,6,FLabour MP Jonathan Brash, whose wife
OL,7,FPamela Hargreaves lost her Hartlepool
OL,8,Fcouncil seat to Farage's party, said
OL,9,Fhe was "looking for change at the top
OL,10,Fof the Labour Party".
OL,12,F"It's clear to me that the prime
OL,13,Fminister should take this opportunity
OL,14,Fto set out a timetable for his own
OL,15,Fdeparture, and then allow for the
OL,16,Fwidest possible leadership election
OL,17,Fthat includes all the talents of our
OL,18,Fparty," he said.
OL,26,@tD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778328667
OL,3,CLabour suffer losses and Reform make
OL,4,Cgains in early election results
OL,6,F"As you can imagine, I'm really angry
OL,7,Fabout tonight, because Labour
OL,8,Fpoliticians are delivering really big
OL,9,Fthings, but we need a leadership of
OL,10,Fthe party that is on the side of the
OL,11,FBritish people," Brash continued.
OL,13,FDeputy Prime Minister David Lammy has
OL,14,Furged his party not to play "pass the
OL,15,Fparcel" with the leadership in
OL,16,Fresponse to the election results, but
OL,17,Ftold the BBC there will be "questions
OL,18,Fthat we have to answer".
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@]OUwD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
